article.headline: Siena 69, Iona 68
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP)Edwin Ubiles swished a baseline jumper with 4.2 seconds left to lead Siena to a 69-68 win over Iona Monday night in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Action. Kenny Hasbrouck led four scorers in double figures for Siena, which beat the Gaels for the sixth straight time. The Saints trailed 68-67 with 8.4 seconds left, down for the first time since midway through the first half, before Ubiles hit the game-winner for two of his 15 points. Iona lost the ball on the ensuing inbound pass and could manage nothing more than a half-court desperation attempt as time expired. The Saints (16-5, 10-0 MAAC) let a 14-point lead slip away in the second before recovering in time to remain undefeated in league play. Ryan Rossiter added 10 points, 12 rebounds and three blocks in the win. Scott Machado had 16 points and eight rebounds for Iona (10-11, 5-5 MAAC).
